#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:213
msgid "### Representation formula (reprFormula)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:215
msgid ""
"By default, a Relation column displays the raw identifier of the linked "
"record. You can define a **representation formula** in MoonScript to show a "
"human-friendly label instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:220
msgid ""
"- The syntax `@field` accesses fields of the linked record.  - FK fields are "
"resolved automatically: `@genre_id.libelle` follows the `genre_id` relation "
"in the linked space and returns its `libelle`.  - Multi-level chaining is "
"supported: `@livre_id.genre_id.libelle` (copy â book â genre).  - If no "
"formula is defined, the column uses the `_repr` field of the target space "
"(if present), otherwise the raw id."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Examples:**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:229
msgid ""
"| Formula | Effect | |---------|-------| | `@nom` | Shows the `nom` field of "
"the linked record | | `@nom .. ' ' .. @prenom` | Concatenates last name and "
"first name | | `@genre_id.libelle` | Follows the FK `genre_id` and displays "
"the genre label | | `@livre_id.genre_id.libelle` | Chains two FKs (copy â "
"book â genre) |"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Concrete example â loans:**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:233
msgid ""
"In the `emprunts` space, the `exemplaire_id` column can display the title of "
"the corresponding book by chaining FKs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:237
msgid "``` reprFormula : @livre_id.titre ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:239
msgid "(To show the book title for this copy.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/get-started.md:241
msgid ""
"To set the formula, click the **(pencil)** next to the Relation field in the "
"Fields panel and enter the representation formula in the **Representation "
"formula** field."
msgstr ""

