#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:26
msgid "## 1. Spaces (tables)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:28
msgid ""
"A **space** is a user-defined data table. It contains **fields** (columns) "
"and **records** (rows)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:30
msgid "### UI Operations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Action    | How |\n"
"|-----------|-----|\n"
"| Create    | Click **+** in the Data section |\n"
"| Rename    | **(pencil)** button in the space toolbar |\n"
"| Delete    | **[del]** (trash can next to the title) |\n"
"| Navigate  | Click the name in the sidebar |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:39 doc/en/reference.md:231 doc/en/reference.md:297
#: doc/en/reference.md:450 doc/en/reference.md:504 doc/en/reference.md:660
msgid "### GraphQL API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# List all spaces\n"
"query {\n"
"  spaces { id name description fields { id name fieldType } }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:56
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Space details, including nested records\n"
"query {\n"
"  space(id: \"...\") {\n"
"    id name fields { id name fieldType formula }\n"
"    records(limit: 10, offset: 0, filter: { field: \"status\", op: EQ, value: \"active\" }) {\n"
"      items { id data }\n"
"      total\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Create\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createSpace(input: { name: \"livres\", description: \"Book catalog\" }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Rename\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  updateSpace(id: \"...\", input: { name: \"new_name\" }) { id name }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:70
msgid "# Delete mutation { deleteSpace(id: \"...\") } ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:74
msgid "## Nested Queries (Nesting)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:76
msgid ""
"In addition to fetching simple relations (FK) directly within records, it is "
"possible to **query collections of related records (back-references) with "
"pagination and filtering directly within a parent query**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:78
msgid "### Back-references with pagination and filtering"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:80
msgid ""
"Dynamically generated back-reference fields (based on inverse relations) "
"support `limit`, `offset`, and `filter` arguments:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# Fetch users and their tasks, filtering tasks by title\n"
"query {\n"
"  users {\n"
"    id\n"
"    username\n"
"    groups {\n"
"      id\n"
"      name\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:96
msgid "### Direct access to space records via `Space.records`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:98
msgid ""
"The `Space` type exposes a `records` field that allows direct retrieval of "
"records from a given space, with pagination and filtering, without going "
"through the root `Query.records`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:111
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# Fetch space details and its first 10 records\n"
"query {\n"
"  space(id: \"my_space_id\") {\n"
"    name\n"
"    records(limit: 10, offset: 0) {\n"
"      items { id data }\n"
"      total\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:115
msgid "## 2. Fields"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:117
msgid ""
"A **field** is a column of a space. Each field has a type, a name, and may "
"have a formula."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:119
msgid "### Available Types"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:133
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Type      | Description |\n"
"|-----------|-------------|\n"
"| `String`  | String |\n"
"| `Int`     | Integer |\n"
"| `Float`   | Decimal number |\n"
"| `Boolean` | Boolean (`true` / `false`) |\n"
"| `UUID`    | Automatically generated UUID |\n"
"| `Sequence`| Auto-increment integer (natural primary key) |\n"
"| `Any`     | Free type (JSON) |\n"
"| `Map`     | JSON object |\n"
"| `Array`   | JSON array |\n"
"| `Datetime`| Date and time |\n"
"| `Relation`| Reference to a record in another space (display customizable via `reprFormula`) |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:135
msgid "### Computed Field (calculated column)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:137
msgid ""
"A computed field evaluates a **MoonScript expression** on each read. The "
"value is **not stored**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:139
msgid ""
"The formula is the body of a function `(self, space) -> <formula>`. In "
"MoonScript, `@field` is a shortcut for `self.field`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Example: `nom_complet` in `auteurs`** â combines first name, particle, and last name, handling null values:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:151
msgid "### Trigger formula"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:153
msgid ""
"A trigger formula is evaluated and its result **stored** on each creation or "
"modification of the record (or only when listed fields in `triggerFields` "
"change)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:155
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Example: `cote_auto` in `livres`** â generates a bibliographic code from the first three letters of the title and the year (triggered on `titre` and `annee`):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:164
msgid "### Formula languages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:169
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Value        | Description |\n"
"|--------------|-------------|\n"
"| `moonscript` | MoonScript (compiled â Lua on the fly) |\n"
"| `lua`        | Native Lua |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:171
msgid "### Helper `space` â access to other spaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:173
msgid ""
"Formulas and triggers receive a second parameter `space` that allows access "
"to all records of another space (full scan):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:183
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```moonscript\n"
"-- Count available copies for this book\n"
"n = 0\n"
"for e in *space(\"exemplaires\")\n"
"  n += 1 if e.livre_id == @id and e.disponible\n"
"n\n"
"-- Get the label of a book's genre\n"
"next(g for g in *space(\"genres\") when g._id == @genre_id)?.libelle\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:185
msgid ""
"`space(\"name\")` returns a Lua list of all records in the space `name`, "
"each record being an object with `_id` (identifier) plus all data fields. "
"Returns `{}` if the space does not exist."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:187
msgid ""
"> **Note:** Full scan is suitable for small spaces (a few thousand records). "
"For large volumes, prefer relations and aggregate widgets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:189
msgid "### Reordering"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:191
msgid "Fields can be reordered by drag-and-drop (::) in the Fields panel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:193
msgid "### Custom Relation Display (`reprFormula`)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:197
msgid ""
"For `Relation` type fields, `reprFormula` controls how the relationship is "
"displayed in the interface (grids, forms, etc.). The formula receives the "
"linked record as parameter (`self`) and must return a string."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Example:** For an `auteur_id` field pointing to the `auteurs` space:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:204
msgid ""
"```moonscript # Display \"First Last\" instead of UUID \"#{@nom} "
"#{@prenom}\" ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:209
msgid ""
"```lua -- Equivalent Lua version return self.nom .. \" \" .. self.prenom ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:211
msgid "### Field Type Conversion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:214
msgid ""
"The `changeFieldType` mutation allows converting a field from one type to "
"another, with an optional conversion formula to transform existing data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:216
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Example:** Convert a `String` field to `Int`:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  changeFieldType(fieldId: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    fieldType: Int,\n"
"    conversionFormula: \"tonumber(self.amount)\",\n"
"    language: \"lua\"\n"
"  }) { id name fieldType }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:229
msgid ""
"If `conversionFormula` is omitted, values are automatically converted when "
"possible, or set to `null` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# Add a simple field\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  addField(spaceId: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    name: \"age\", fieldType: Int, notNull: false\n"
"  }) { id name }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:248
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Add a computed column\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  addField(spaceId: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    name: \"nom_complet\", fieldType: String,\n"
"    formula: \"parts = {}\\ntable.insert(parts, @prenom) if @prenom and @prenom != \\\"\\\"\\ntable.insert(parts, @particule) if @particule and @particule != \\\"\\\"\\ntable.insert(parts, @nom) if @nom and @nom != \\\"\\\"\\ntable.concat(parts, \\\" \\\" )\",\n"
"    language: \"moonscript\"\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:258
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Add a trigger formula (triggered on change of \"titre\" or \"annee\")\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  addField(spaceId: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    name: \"cote_auto\", fieldType: String,\n"
"    formula: \"prefix = (@titre or \\\"\\\")\\\\upper!\\\\sub(1, 3)\\\\gsub(\\\"[^%A]\\\", \\\"\\\")\\nannee  = if @annee then tostring(@annee) else \\\"????\\\"\\n\\\"#{prefix}-#{annee}\\\"\",\n"
"    triggerFields: [\"titre\", \"annee\"],\n"
"    language: \"moonscript\"\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:266
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Update an existing field\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  updateField(fieldId: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    formula: \"self.prenom .. \\\" \\\" .. self.nom\",\n"
"    language: \"lua\"\n"
"  }) { id name formula }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:269
msgid "# Delete mutation { removeField(fieldId: \"...\") }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:277
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Reorder\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  reorderFields(\n"
"    spaceId: \"...\",\n"
"    fieldIds: [\"id1\", \"id2\", \"id3\"]\n"
"  ) { id position }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:287
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Change field type\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  changeFieldType(fieldId: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    fieldType: Int,\n"
"    conversionFormula: \"tonumber(self.amount)\",\n"
"    language: \"lua\"\n"
"  }) { id name fieldType }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:291
msgid "## 3. Relations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:293
msgid ""
"A **relation** links a field of a space (field of type `Relation`) to "
"another space. It enables dependent filtering in custom views."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:295
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Recursive relations** (to the same space) are supported, for modeling tree structures (e.g., categories, genealogies).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:305
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# List relations of a space\n"
"query {\n"
"  relations(spaceId: \"...\") {\n"
"    id name fromFieldId toSpaceId toFieldId reprFormula\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:316
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Create a relation livres â auteurs\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createRelation(input: {\n"
"    name: \"livre_auteur\",\n"
"    fromSpaceId: \"livres-id\",\n"
"    fromFieldId: \"auteur_id-field-id\",\n"
"    toSpaceId:   \"auteurs-id\",\n"
"    toFieldId:   \"id-field-id\"\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:327
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Create a relation livres â genres\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createRelation(input: {\n"
"    name: \"livre_genre\",\n"
"    fromSpaceId: \"livres-id\",\n"
"    fromFieldId: \"genre_id-field-id\",\n"
"    toSpaceId:   \"genres-id\",\n"
"    toFieldId:   \"id-field-id\"\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:338
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Create a relation exemplaires â livres\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createRelation(input: {\n"
"    name: \"exemplaire_livre\",\n"
"    fromSpaceId: \"exemplaires-id\",\n"
"    fromFieldId: \"livre_id-field-id\",\n"
"    toSpaceId:   \"livres-id\",\n"
"    toFieldId:   \"id-field-id\"\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:341
msgid "# Delete mutation { deleteRelation(id: \"...\") }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:351
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Set the display formula for a relation livres â auteurs\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  updateRelation(id: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    reprFormula: \"(@particule and @particule .. ' ' or '') .. @nom .. (@prenom and ' ' .. @prenom or '')\"\n"
"  }) {\n"
"    id reprFormula\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:353
msgid "### Display formula"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:355
msgid ""
"A relation can have a **`reprFormula`** field: a MoonScript expression "
"evaluated on each target record to produce a readable label."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:363
msgid ""
"- The variable `self` (accessible via `@field`) is bound to the target "
"record.  - Examples: `@libelle`, `@nom .. ' ' .. @prenom` - FK fields are "
"automatically resolved: `@genre_id.libelle` follows the `genre_id` relation "
"and returns the `libelle` field of the corresponding genres record.  - "
"Chaining is possible over several levels: `@livre_id.genre_id.libelle` "
"(exemplaire â livre â genre).  - When defined, FK columns in the grid "
"display the formula result instead of the raw identifier.  - In edit mode, a "
"dropdown lists all target records with their computed label.  - If no "
"formula is defined, the column uses the `_repr` field of the target space "
"(if it exists), otherwise the raw identifier."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:367
msgid "## 4. Data (records)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:369
msgid "### Editing in the grid"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:374
msgid ""
"- Click a cell to enter edit mode.  - **Enter** or **Tab** to validate and "
"move to the next cell.  - Empty row at the bottom: type to create a new "
"record.  - Check one or more rows then click **[del]** to delete."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:376
msgid "### Filtering"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:378
msgid "The API supports composable filtering:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:397
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"query {\n"
"  records(\n"
"    spaceId: \"...\"\n"
"    filter: {\n"
"      or: [\n"
"        { field: \"titre\", op: STARTS_WITH, value: \"Le\" }\n"
"        { field: \"annee\", op: GTE, value: \"2000\" }\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"    limit: 50\n"
"    offset: 0\n"
"  ) {\n"
"    items { id data }\n"
"    total\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:399
msgid "### Filter operators"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:408
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Operator      | Meaning |\n"
"|---------------|---------|\n"
"| `EQ`          | Equal to |\n"
"| `NEQ`         | Not equal to |\n"
"| `LT` / `GT`   | Less / greater (strict) |\n"
"| `LTE` / `GTE` | Less / greater or equal |\n"
"| `CONTAINS`    | Contains substring |\n"
"| `STARTS_WITH` | Starts with |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:410
msgid "### Formula filters and FK traversal"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:412
msgid ""
"In addition to field/operator filters, you can express arbitrary conditions "
"in **MoonScript** via `formula`. These formulas have access to the **FK "
"proxy**: relation fields are automatically resolved to the linked record, "
"and multi-level chaining is supported."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:424
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# Filter books whose genre is 'Roman' (via FK traversal)\n"
"query {\n"
"  records(\n"
"    spaceId: \"livres-id\"\n"
"    filter: { formula: \"@genre_id.libelle == 'Roman'\", language: \"moonscript\" }\n"
"  ) {\n"
"    items { id data }\n"
"    total\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:436
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Filter copies whose book belongs to genre 'Polar' (2 levels)\n"
"query {\n"
"  records(\n"
"    spaceId: \"exemplaires-id\"\n"
"    filter: { formula: \"@livre_id.genre_id.libelle == 'Polar'\", language: \"moonscript\" }\n"
"  ) {\n"
"    items { id data }\n"
"    total\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:438
msgid "FK formulas also work in **dynamic queries** generated for each space:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:446
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"query {\n"
"  livres(filter: { formula: \"@genre_id.libelle == 'Roman'\", language: \"moonscript\" }) {\n"
"    items { titre }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:448
msgid ""
"> **Note:** FK resolution first tries direct access by primary key "
"(efficient), with fallback to a full scan for non-PK references. For large "
"spaces, prefer classic field filters when possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:458
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# Read records\n"
"query {\n"
"  records(spaceId: \"...\", limit: 100) {\n"
"    items { id data } total\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:461
msgid ""
"# Read a single record query { record(spaceId: \"...\", id: \"42\") { id "
"data } }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:469
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Insert an author\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  insertRecord(\n"
"    spaceId: \"...\",\n"
"    data: { nom: \"Hugo\", prenom: \"Victor\", particule: \"\" }\n"
"  ) { id data }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:477
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Insert a book\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  insertRecord(\n"
"    spaceId: \"...\",\n"
"    data: { titre: \"Les MisÃ©rables\", auteur_id: 1, genre_id: 2, annee: 1862, isbn: \"978-2-07-040850-4\" }\n"
"  ) { id data }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:485
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Insert a copy\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  insertRecord(\n"
"    spaceId: \"...\",\n"
"    data: { livre_id: 1, etat: \"bon\", disponible: true }\n"
"  ) { id data }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:492
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Update\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  updateRecord(spaceId: \"...\", id: \"42\", data: { nom: \"Martin\" }) {\n"
"    id data\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:496
msgid "# Delete mutation { deleteRecord(spaceId: \"...\", id: \"42\") } ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:500
msgid "## 5. Classic Views"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:502
msgid ""
"Classic views are named display configurations for a space (grid, form, or "
"gallery type). Currently, only the `grid` type is fully supported."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:513
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# Create a grid view on the book catalog\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createView(\n"
"    spaceId: \"...\",\n"
"    input: { name: \"Catalog\", viewType: grid }\n"
"  ) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:518
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Update\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  updateView(id: \"...\", input: { name: \"New name\" }) { id name }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:522
msgid "# Delete mutation { deleteView(id: \"...\") } ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:526
msgid "## 6. Custom Views (YAML)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:528
msgid "Custom views are multi-space dashboards declared in YAML."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:530
msgid "### Editor"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:532
msgid "Click **âEditâ** on a view to open a fullscreen modal composed of:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:535
msgid ""
"- A **CodeMirror** editor (YAML, monokai theme) for direct YAML editing.  - "
"An **interactive ERD diagram** on the right: clicking a field automatically "
"generates the corresponding YAML in the editor (widget, columns, "
"`depends_on` if FK detected)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:538
msgid ""
"Each ERD box has a pseudo-field **`*`** (first row) that adds the space "
"without column restriction (no `columns` key in YAML).  Fields are sorted "
"**alphabetically**. Self-relations (e.g., `parent_id â id`) are shown as a "
"loop on the right side of the box."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:540
msgid "### Basic structure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:548
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"layout:\n"
"  direction: vertical    # or horizontal\n"
"  children:\n"
"    - widget: ...        # leaf widget (data grid)\n"
"    - layout: ...        # nested area (recursive)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:550
msgid "### Widget"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:563
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"widget:\n"
"  id: unique_identifier   # required, unique in the view\n"
"  title: \"Displayed title\"   # optional\n"
"  space: space_name        # Tarantool space name\n"
"  columns: [field1, field2]  # displayed columns (default: all)\n"
"  factor: 2                  # weight in parent area (default: 1)\n"
"  depends_on:                # dependent filtering (optional)\n"
"    widget: parent_widget_id\n"
"    field: join_field        # field in THIS space\n"
"    from_field: id           # field in parent widget (default: id)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:565
msgid "### Dependencies (inter-widget filtering)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:567
msgid ""
"When `depends_on` is set, the widget only displays records whose `field` "
"matches the value of `from_field` in the selected row of the parent widget."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:569
msgid "### Proportional factors"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:571
msgid ""
"The `factor` indicates the relative space taken by a child in its area. "
"Example: if widget A has `factor: 2` and widget B `factor: 1`, A takes up "
"2/3 of the space."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:573
msgid "### Custom columns"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:577
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"columns: [prenom, nom, email]   # only these fields, in this order\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:579
msgid "If omitted, all fields of the space are displayed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:581
msgid "### Full example"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:583
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Library management** view: book catalog â copies â current loans, with an aggregate widget for loans by genre.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:617
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"layout:\n"
"  direction: vertical\n"
"  children:\n"
"    - widget:\n"
"        id: livres\n"
"        title: Book catalog\n"
"        space: livres\n"
"        columns: [titre, cote_auto, auteur_id, genre_id, isbn, annee]\n"
"    - layout:\n"
"        direction: horizontal\n"
"        children:\n"
"          - widget:\n"
"              id: exemplaires\n"
"              title: Copies\n"
"              space: exemplaires\n"
"              depends_on:\n"
"                widget: livres\n"
"                field: livre_id\n"
"                from_field: id\n"
"              columns: [etat, disponible]\n"
"              factor: 2\n"
"          - widget:\n"
"              id: emprunts\n"
"              title: Current loans\n"
"              space: emprunts\n"
"              depends_on:\n"
"                widget: exemplaires\n"
"                field: exemplaire_id\n"
"                from_field: id\n"
"              columns: [personne_id, date_emprunt, date_retour]\n"
"              factor: 3\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:619
msgid "### Aggregate widget"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:621
msgid ""
"A widget of type `aggregate` displays a read-only summary table, computed "
"server-side by iterating over the space. It is equivalent to a SQL `GROUP "
"BY`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:632
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"widget:\n"
"  type: aggregate\n"
"  title: \"Loans by genre\"\n"
"  space: emprunts\n"
"  groupBy: [genre_id]\n"
"  aggregate:\n"
"    - fn: count\n"
"      as: nb_emprunts\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:634
msgid ""
"The `as` alias is optional: if absent, the generated column name is "
"`fn_field` (e.g., `avg_annee`) or `count` for `COUNT(*)`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:636
msgid "#### Computed columns"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:638
msgid ""
"You can add client-side computed columns via the `computed` key. Each entry "
"provides an alias (`as`) and a JavaScript expression (`expr`) evaluated on "
"each aggregated row. The `row` object contains all `groupBy` fields and "
"`aggregate` aliases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:654
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"widget:\n"
"  type: aggregate\n"
"  title: \"Loans by genre\"\n"
"  space: emprunts\n"
"  groupBy: [genre_id]\n"
"  aggregate:\n"
"    - fn: count\n"
"      as: nb_emprunts\n"
"  computed:\n"
"    - as: label\n"
"      expr: \"row.genre_id + ' (' + row.nb_emprunts + ')'\"\n"
"    - as: status\n"
"      expr: \"row.nb_emprunts > 10 ? 'Active' : 'Low activity'\"\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:656
msgid ""
"> **Note:** `computed` expressions are pure JavaScript (not MoonScript); "
"they run in the browser after receiving the aggregated data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:658
msgid "![Aggregate widget](../img/aggregate-widget.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:664
msgid "```graphql # List query { customViews { id name yaml } }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:672
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Create\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createCustomView(input: {\n"
"    name: \"Dashboard\",\n"
"    yaml: \"layout:\\n  direction: vertical\\n  children: []\\n\"\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:677
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Update\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  updateCustomView(id: \"...\", input: { yaml: \"...\" }) { id yaml }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:680
msgid "# Delete mutation { deleteCustomView(id: \"...\") }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:692
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Direct aggregate query: loans by genre\n"
"query {\n"
"  aggregateSpace(\n"
"    spaceName: \"emprunts\",\n"
"    groupBy: [\"genre_id\"],\n"
"    aggregate: [\n"
"      { fn: \"count\", as: \"nb_emprunts\" }\n"
"    ]\n"
"  )\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:696
msgid "## 7. Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:698
msgid ""
"TGui uses **Bearer tokens** (SHA-256 + salt, stored in Tarantool session). "
"The token is persisted in `localStorage` and automatically sent by the "
"client."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:700
msgid "### Login flow"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:709
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  login(username: \"alice\", password: \"secret\") {\n"
"    token\n"
"    user { id username email groups { id name } }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:711
msgid "The token is then sent in the HTTP header:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:715
msgid "``` Authorization: Bearer <token> ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:717
msgid "### Logout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:721
msgid "```graphql mutation { logout } ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:723
msgid "### Current user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:727
msgid "```graphql query { me { id username email groups { id name } } } ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:729
msgid "### Change own password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:735
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  changePassword(currentPassword: \"old\", newPassword: \"new\")\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:739
msgid "## 8. Users and Groups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:741
msgid "These operations require **membership in the `admin` group**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:747
msgid ""
"```graphql # List query { users { id username email groups { id name } } }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:756
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Create (admin only)\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createUser(input: {\n"
"    username: \"bob\",\n"
"    email: \"bob@ex.com\",\n"
"    password: \"secret\"\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:762
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Force password change (admin only)\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  adminSetPassword(userId: \"...\", newPassword: \"new\")\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:774
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# List (with members and permissions)\n"
"query {\n"
"  groups {\n"
"    id name description\n"
"    members { id username }\n"
"    permissions { id resourceType resourceId level }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:779
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Create\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  createGroup(input: { name: \"editors\", description: \"...\" }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:782
msgid "# Delete mutation { deleteGroup(id: \"...\") }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:785
msgid "# Add member mutation { addMember(userId: \"...\", groupId: \"...\") }"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:789
msgid ""
"# Remove member mutation { removeMember(userId: \"...\", groupId: \"...\") } "
"```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:793
msgid "## 9. Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:795
msgid "Permissions are granted to a **group** on a resource."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:801
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Level   | Description |\n"
"|---------|-------------|\n"
"| `read`  | Read-only |\n"
"| `write` | Read + write |\n"
"| `admin` | Full control of the resource |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:811
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```graphql\n"
"# Grant a permission\n"
"mutation {\n"
"  grant(groupId: \"...\", input: {\n"
"    resourceType: \"space\",\n"
"    resourceId: \"...\",\n"
"    level: write\n"
"  }) { id }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:815
msgid "# Revoke mutation { revoke(permissionId: \"...\") } ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:819
msgid "## 10. Export and Import Snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:821
msgid ""
"The **Export / Import** section of the Admin panel lets you save the entire "
"TGui application (schema, custom views, groups, permissions, and optionally "
"data) to a `.tdb.yaml` file, then restore it on another instance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:823
msgid "### Export"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:825
msgid "Two export modes are available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:828
msgid ""
"- **Structure only** (`exportSnapshot(includeData: false)`): exports the "
"full schema (spaces, fields, relations, custom views, groups, permissions) "
"without data. Useful for sharing an application model.  - **Structure + "
"data** (`exportSnapshot(includeData: true)`): also exports all rows of each "
"space. Useful for a full backup or migration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:830
msgid "The produced file is readable YAML:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:915
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"version: \"1\"\n"
"exported_at: \"2026-03-08T12:00:00\"\n"
"schema:\n"
"  spaces:\n"
"    - name: auteurs\n"
"      fields:\n"
"        - name: particule\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          notNull: false\n"
"        - name: nom\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          notNull: true\n"
"        - name: prenom\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          notNull: false\n"
"        - name: nom_complet\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          formula: \"=> parts = {}\\ntable.insert(parts, @prenom) if @prenom and @prenom != \\\"\\\"\\ntable.insert(parts, @particule) if @particule and @particule != \\\"\\\"\\ntable.insert(parts, @nom) if @nom and @nom != \\\"\\\"\\ntable.concat(parts, \\\" \\\" )\"\n"
"          language: moonscript\n"
"    - name: genres\n"
"      fields:\n"
"        - name: libelle\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          notNull: true\n"
"    - name: livres\n"
"      fields:\n"
"        - name: titre\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          notNull: true\n"
"        - name: auteur_id\n"
"          fieldType: Relation\n"
"          notNull: false\n"
"        - name: genre_id\n"
"          fieldType: Relation\n"
"          notNull: false\n"
"        - name: cote\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          notNull: false\n"
"        - name: isbn\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          notNull: false\n"
"        - name: annee\n"
"          fieldType: Int\n"
"          notNull: false\n"
"        - name: cote_auto\n"
"          fieldType: String\n"
"          formula: \"=> prefix = (@titre or \\\"\\\")\\\\upper!\\\\sub(1, 3)\\\\gsub(\\\"[^%A]\\\", \\\"\\\")\\nannee  = if @annee then tostring(@annee) else \\\"????\\\"\\n\\\"#{prefix}-#{annee}\\\"\"\n"
"          triggerFields: [titre, annee]\n"
"          language: moonscript\n"
"      views:\n"
"        - name: Catalog\n"
"          viewType: Grid\n"
"  relations:\n"
"    - fromSpace: livres\n"
"      fromField: auteur_id\n"
"      toSpace: auteurs\n"
"      toField: id\n"
"    - fromSpace: livres\n"
"      fromField: genre_id\n"
"      toSpace: genres\n"
"      toField: id\n"
"    - fromSpace: exemplaires\n"
"      fromField: livre_id\n"
"      toSpace: livres\n"
"      toField: id\n"
"  custom_views:\n"
"    - name: Library management\n"
"      yaml: |\n"
"        layout: â¦\n"
"  groups:\n"
"    - name: admin\n"
"      members: [admin]\n"
"      permissions:\n"
"        - resourceType: space\n"
"          level: admin\n"
"data:                    # absent if structure only export\n"
"  auteurs:\n"
"    - {nom: Hugo, prenom: Victor}\n"
"  genres:\n"
"    - {libelle: Roman}\n"
"  livres:\n"
"    - {titre: \"Les MisÃ©rables\", auteur_id: 1, genre_id: 1, annee: 1862}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:917
msgid ""
"Internal identifiers are excluded; matching on import is done by **name**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/en/reference.md:919
msgid "### Import"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: doc/en/reference.md:926
msgid ""
"TGui automatically computes a **diff** between the file's schema and the "
"current schema, and displays it with color codes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   - '
#: doc/en/reference.md:926
msgid "green **Create**: the item will be added."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   - '
#: doc/en/reference.md:926
msgid "red **Delete**: the item will be removed (Replace mode only)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   - '
#: doc/en/reference.md:926
msgid "orange **Modify**: a field's type has changed."
